The paper deals with the construction of Steiner systems from cyclic codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves combinatorial designs (cs.DM) and coding theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of the constructed systems, which may have implications for cryptography (cs.CR) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
